# Project Startup & Common Development Commands

**Note:** All commands below are written to be run from the project root (`/Users/sojanvarghese/Documents/ai/webhooks`). You can run them from anywhere by using the full relative path.

## Start Servers
- Start Rails backend:
  ```sh
  (cd webhooks-backend && rails server -p 3001)
  ```
- Start React frontend:
  ```sh
  (cd webhooks-frontend && npm start)
  ```
- Visit the app at: [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000)

## Common Commands
- **Install backend dependencies:**
  ```sh
  (cd webhooks-backend && bundle install)
  ```
- **Install frontend dependencies:**
  ```sh
  (cd webhooks-frontend && yarn install)
  # or
  (cd webhooks-frontend && npm install)
  ```
- **Run backend migrations:**
  ```sh
  (cd webhooks-backend && rails db:create db:migrate)
  ```
- **Stop Rails server (if stuck):**
  ```sh
  kill -9 $(cat webhooks-backend/tmp/pids/server.pid)
  ```
- **Build frontend for production:**
  ```sh
  (cd webhooks-frontend && npm run build)
  ```
- **Run frontend tests:**
  ```sh
  (cd webhooks-frontend && npm test)
  ```
- **Run backend tests:**
  ```sh
  (cd webhooks-backend && bundle exec rspec)
  # or
  (cd webhooks-backend && rails test)
  ```

---

> These commands are always available for quick reference and should be used for local development and troubleshooting. They are safe to run from any directory within the project.
